{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17510865","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17510865"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:34:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:34:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11654"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11654"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.03,0.05,0.1,0.67]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4275"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80653"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4275","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4275"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11654"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65949"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"354"},{"type":"tags","id":"461"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1144"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3892"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7901"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8188"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26973"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43874"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44786"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44948"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80653","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80653"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 57-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-month history of increasing difficulty swallowing and hoarseness. During this time, he has lost 5 kg of weight. His medical history includes achalasia, for which he had a cardiomyotomy fourteen years ago. He has a 20 pack-year smoking history and drinks about two cans of beer a day. On examination, he appears pale, but no other abnormalities are found. Indirect laryngoscopy shows a left vocal cord palsy, and a CT scan is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Carcinoma of the larynx","Carcinoma of the piriform fossa","Carcinoma of the thyroid","Carcinoma of the lung","Carcinoma of the oesophagus"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst any of the listed options could produce this clinical picture, the most likely underlying problem is a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarcinoma of the oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E (Image). Hoarseness is a worrying symptom and in these circumstances is very likely to be due to vocal cord palsy. Any of the listed tumours could be situated close to the recurrent laryngeal nerve. Tumour extension and compression of this nerve could lead to vocal cord palsy. The CT scan shows a bulky tumour in the mid-oesophagus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOesophageal cancer is the sixth most common cause of death from cancer and the eighth most common cancer in the world. Whilst most of these lesions were once squamous cell tumours, adenocarcinoma is now the most common histological type in western communities. The two important risk factors associated with squamous type are smoking and chronic alcohol consumption. Less common risk factors include caustic injury, achalasia and chronic consumption of scalding hot liquids.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAchalasia is an idiopathic oesophageal motility disorder with disordered peristalsis and absence of lower oesophageal sphincter relaxation. Development of oesophageal cancer is an uncommon, but important potential complication of long-standing achalasia. However, this particular individual is a heavy smoker and regular consumer of alcohol - which are more important risk factors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the larynx\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Epyriform fossa\u003C/strong\u003E may present with hoarseness and certainly most cases are associated with heavy smoking and alcohol abuse. Difficulty in swallowing is not a particularly common presenting symptom. \u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the lung\u003C/strong\u003E usually presents with increasing cough associated with haemoptysis. Hoarseness of voice and laryngeal palsy can also be seen. Dysphagia would be an unusual symptom.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the thyroid\u003C/strong\u003E usually presents with a neck mass with or without dysthyroidism. Dysphagia would be a very uncommon presenting symptom.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Oesophageal cancer is the sixth leading cause of death from cancer and the eighth most common cancer in the world.","Smoking is one of the major risk factors for developing oesophageal squamous carcinoma.","Hoarseness in oesophageal cancer can result from recurrent laryngeal nerve involvement due to tumour extension."],"references":["Cavallin F, Scarpa M, Cagol M, Alfieri R, Ruol A, Sileni VC, Ancona E, Castoro C. Esophageal Cancer Clinical Presentation: Trends in the Last 3 Decades in a Large Italian Series. Ann Surg. 2018 Jan;267(1):99-104. doi: 10.1097/SLA.0000000000002048. PMID: 27759616. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27759616/","Patterson RH, Fischman VG, Wasserman I, Siu J, Shrime MG, Fagan JJ, Koch W, Alkire BC. Global Burden of Head and Neck Cancer: Economic Consequences, Health, and the Role of Surgery. Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2020 Mar;162(3):296-303. doi: 10.1177/0194599819897265. Epub 2020 Jan 7. PMID: 31906785. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31906785/","Wang Y, Mukkamalla SKR, Singh R, Babiker HM, Lyons S. Esophageal Cancer. 2024 Aug 17. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29083661. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29083661/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65949"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11654"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20267"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20356"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20267","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20267"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/KtwvvLe0eh3vNMLrxpkdk9Dn4H4Pg7.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/KtwvvLe0eh3vNMLrxpkdk9Dn4H4Pg7.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":630,"height":621}},{"type":"media","id":"20356","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20356"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/gBZtPT3C9gy219yXI209iWLLXh2WBg.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/gBZtPT3C9gy219yXI209iWLLXh2WBg.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":630,"height":621}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65949","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65949"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T06:55:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-22T06:56:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4275"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80653"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"